  "response": "Cardiac muscle is a specialized type of muscle tissue found only in the heart. Here are some specific examples of cardiac muscles:\n\n1. Heart chambers\n- Left ventricle\n- Right ventricle\n- Left atrium\n- Right atrium\n\n2. Parts of the heart wall\n- Myocardium (middle layer of the heart wall)\n- Cardiac muscle fibers\n\n3. Heart-specific structures\n- Papillary muscles\n- Trabeculae carneae\n- Septum muscles\n\n4. Cardiac muscle regions\n- Heart apex\n- Heart base\n- Interventricular septum\n\n5. Specialized cardiac muscle structures\n- Sinoatrial (SA) node\n- Atrioventricular (AV) node\n\nThese cardiac muscles work together to:\n- Contract and relax rhythmically\n- Pump blood throughout the body\n- Maintain heart's pumping action\n- Control heart rate and electrical signals\n\nCardiac muscles are unique because they are:\n- Involuntary\n- Striated\n- Self-exciting\n- Connected by intercalated discs\n- Capable of continuous, coordinated contractions",
